node.text: Why do today what you could hold off 'till tomorrow (or next week)? I'm working on a BIG project, and of course, big projects call for even BIGGER procrastination. So here's this little series (that we'll make whenever we want, and won't whenever we don't) where you can watch me work on things I don't need to be working on. Please enjoy.

node.text: It’s grilling and chilling weather and thankfully, my @WeberGrills SmokeFire Grill makes the chill part so easy. #WeberAd Just add pellets and you're ready to smoke, roast, grill, and even bake! Hang out with your guests while the Weber Connect App makes it a cinch to keep an eye on all the grilling action! For an easy taco party with friends, I developed a simple smoked chicken recipe I’d like to call Pollito Pibil 🍗  It has all the flavors of cochinita pibil, but you know, chicken! Head to the link in my stories to save $200 off your very own #WeberSmokeFire and find the full recipes on hellosohla.com #DiscoverWhatsPossible

node.text: I’m celebrating this 4th with friends, family, and an entire leg of lamb, slow-smoked and roasted on my @WeberGrills SmokeFire Grill! #WeberAd This all-in-one wood pellet grill can handle anything—low-temp, high-temp, and most importantly, accurate temps! 🔥 This grill heats more consistently and evenly than my kitchen oven, which means summer baking just got easier. Smoked and grilled baklava for dessert? Yes, please! ​Find the full recipes on hellosohla.com #DiscoverWhatsPossible #WeberSmokeFire

node.text:
Please enjoy this (only sometimes blurry) instructional video. Shot by @hamegram Autofocus by @lumixusa

Mixed Greens Spanakopita
1 pound chopped tender greens and herbs
1/2 cup white rice, rinsed, soaked, and crushed
3 spring onions
2 garlic cloves
1 teaspoon kosher salt
1 large egg
8 ounces feta cheese
6 to 8 sheets phyllo dough
melted butter or olive oil

10-inch cast iron skillet

Bake at 400F for 45 minutes

node.text:
Hospitals in India are overwhelmed with COVID patients and need our help! Donate at least $50 to Mission Oxygen (link in bio) and email your donation receipt to hellosohla@gmail.com to be entered into a raffle to win a cooking class with me and @chetnamakan ! 

You have until Wednesday 5/5 6pm EST to enter. 10 winners will be announced on Friday! The private cooking class will be on Sunday 5/9! Good luck!

node.text: Watch this full-length, directors cut of me making caramel in (practically) real time. I talk about your caramel fears, hopes, and dreams, and cover where you've gone wrong so you can prevent good sugar from going bad. Also, I make a gluten-free, dairy-free version for all my dietary restriction friends! Find the recipe at the link in my bio and @food52

node.text:
#ad I teamed up with @hbomax to create a dish inspired by one of my favorite shows, HBO’s Game of Thrones! Remember when Arya was all about that revenge life and surprised Walder Frey with a pie made of his SONS??

This Sons of Frey Savory Meat Pie is inspired by that unforgettable moment—but made appetizing with short ribs braised in chicken bone broth (double meat!) and stained blood-red with roasted beets❗️It's topped with a flaky pie crust and baked until golden brown and bubbly 🥧 I like to eat it while rewatching that scene, then maybe skipping back to watch Arya take Ser Meryn's eyes, or ahead to when she fakes out the Night King ❄ 

With HBO Max, I can stream all the titles I love from any of my devices! Head to the link above to sign up today!

node.text:
Have your own dosa party! 

Rinse and soak overnight: 
2 cups white rice
2/3 cup urad dal (or any husked lentil) 
1/2 teaspoon fenugreek (optional)

Drain and blend with 1 teaspoon kosher salt and enough water to make a thin batter

Let ferment in a warm place until doubled in size (12 to 48 hours)

Then all you need to do is cook and fill with whatever your hearts desires!

node.text: It's our third (and final, maybe?) episode! Hope you enjoy, and who knows, perhaps we'll shoot some more the next time I don't want to work on stuff I should be working on.
Thanks @lallimusic for coming to our ancient gnocchi party! You’re all invited too, head to the @history YouTube to check it out!

node.text: You may need to sit down for this one (at least, I do). Friends, I really did it this time. Is this my favorite recipe of all time????? Maybe! Sweet and savory cheesy chewy mochi cake with POPS of corn and chili flake! Upside down mochi cake with big wedges of peach and pockets of sticky saucy caramel! Make one, make both, make your own using my guide to all things mochi cake on @food52 Link in bio!

node.text: Why do today what you could hold off 'till tomorrow (or next week)? I'm working on a BIG project, and of course, big projects call for even BIGGER procrastination. So here's this little series (that we'll make whenever we want, and won't whenever we don't) where you can watch me work on things I don't need to be working on. Please enjoy.

user.full_name: h e l e n a

node.text: This Ancient Recipes I make not one, but TWO ancient cheesecakes! Honestly, I wasn’t sure about either, but they both turned out pretty delicious and once again taught me something new. Head over to the @history YouTube channel to check it out! (Oh, and they let me keep the ancient Roman terracotta oven 🎉)
